    {
      "id": "nodeset-first-wave-holes",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Observed Holes",
      "position": {
        "x": 1780,
        "y": 240
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Observed Holes\n\nFrom actual planning-graph usage, the current set is strong on work, decisions, and constraints, but thinner on **belief** and **time**.\n\nMost likely missing node types:\n\n- `assumption`\n  - for provisional beliefs that are neither decisions nor open questions\n- `milestone`\n  - for release checkpoints and horizon markers that are not ordinary tasks\n\nPossible later additions, but less urgent:\n\n- `investigation`\n  - if open questions need a stronger research/execution shape\n- `evidence` or `reference-note`\n  - if planning graphs need to preserve why a conclusion is trusted\n\nWhat does **not** look like a hole right now:\n\n- `status` and `owner` as standalone nodes\n- these are working better as fields on the current planning types",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "isRoot": false,
        "root": false,
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
